hands_on_practices.solution:
We apply the WKB quantization condition for a one‐dimensional bound state with quantum number $n=0$,
$$\int_{x_1}^{x_2}p(x)\,dx = \left(n+\tfrac12\right)\pi\hbar
\quad\text{with}\quad
p(x)=\sqrt{2m\bigl[E - V(x)\bigr]}\,. $$

1. At the threshold of binding $E\to0^-$, the classical turning points tend to $x_1\to-\infty$, $x_2\to+\infty$.  Thus
$$p(x)\approx \sqrt{2m\bigl[0 -(-V_0e^{-x^2/a^2})\bigr]}
=\sqrt{2mV_0}\,\exp\!\bigl(-\tfrac{x^2}{2a^2}\bigr)\,. $$

2. The WKB integral becomes
$$I=\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}p(x)\,dx
=\sqrt{2mV_0}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}e^{-x^2/(2a^2)}\,dx
=\sqrt{2mV_0}\,\bigl(a\sqrt{2\pi}\bigr)
=2a\sqrt{\pi mV_0}\,. $$

3. Setting $I=(0+\tfrac12)\pi\hbar=\tfrac{\pi\hbar}{2}$ yields
$$2a\sqrt{\pi mV_0}=\frac{\pi\hbar}{2}
\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
\sqrt{\pi mV_0}=\frac{\pi\hbar}{4a}
\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
\pi mV_0=\frac{\pi^2\hbar^2}{16a^2}
\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
V_0=\frac{\pi\hbar^2}{16m\,a^2}\,. $$
